00:50:10,120 --> 00:50:13,360
Judy, I have your
person-to-person from New Penzance.

621
00:50:13,440 --> 00:50:14,480
Go ahead, New Penzance.

622
00:50:15,120 --> 00:50:16,600
Hello, this is Captain Sharp.

623
00:50:16,680 --> 00:50:19,040
Hello, Captain Sharp.
This is Social Services.

624
00:50:19,120 --> 00:50:21,720
I'm calling in reference to Sam
Shakusky, ward of the state.

625
00:50:21,800 --> 00:50:22,960
I understand he's
in your custody.

626
00:50:23,040 --> 00:50:24,160
That's correct.

627
00:50:24,240 --> 00:50:26,080
What's his condition?
Has he suffered

628
00:50:26,160 --> 00:50:28,400
any injury or
trauma of any kind?

629
00:50:28,480 --> 00:50:30,200
- He's fine.
- Very good.

630
00:50:30,320 --> 00:50:31,640
How do I get to you?

631
00:50:31,720 --> 00:50:33,240
The fastest way
would be sea plane.

632
00:50:33,360 --> 00:50:34,920
Jed can bring you
in with the mail.

633
00:50:35,000 --> 00:50:36,920
I'll come tomorrow morning,
if that's acceptable to you.

634
00:50:37,000 --> 00:50:38,760
Is someone able to
provide reasonable care

635
00:50:38,840 --> 00:50:40,480
and nourishment for
the boy until that time?

636
00:50:42,680 --> 00:50:43,720
Is that a yes?

637
00:50:46,920 --> 00:50:49,720
Very good, I'll contact you
again before the end of the day.

638
00:50:49,800 --> 00:50:50,880
Wait a second.

639
00:50:50,960 --> 00:50:52,200
Yes?

640
00:50:52,280 --> 00:50:53,440
Social Services?

641
00:50:53,520 --> 00:50:54,720
Captain Sharp?

642
00:50:55,840 --> 00:50:57,680
What's going to happen to him?

643
00:51:00,120 --> 00:51:03,440
Well, normally,
we try to place him in another foster home,

644
00:51:03,520 --> 00:51:05,640
but that option's no
longer available to us,

645
00:51:05,720 --> 00:51:07,920
in my opinion,
due to his case history.

646
00:51:08,000 --> 00:51:10,240
Which means he'll go
to Juvenile Refuge.

647
00:51:10,640 --> 00:51:13,160
Wait. What does that mean?
Is that an orphanage?

648
00:51:13,800 --> 00:51:14,840
Who's speaking?

649
00:51:15,280 --> 00:51:17,000
This is Scout Master
Randy Ward.

650
00:51:19,480 --> 00:51:21,040
Right, an orphanage.

651
00:51:25,080 --> 00:51:27,920
But the first step is
the admissions panel

652
00:51:28,000 --> 00:51:29,680
requires
a psychological evaluation

653
00:51:29,760 --> 00:51:32,160
to determine
whether or not the boy

654
00:51:32,240 --> 00:51:34,200
is a candidate for
institutional treatment

655
00:51:34,280 --> 00:51:36,800
or electroshock therapy.

656
00:51:36,920 --> 00:51:38,880
Excuse me. Shock therapy?

657
00:51:38,960 --> 00:51:41,120
Why would that
be called for? He's not violent.

658
00:51:41,640 --> 00:51:44,120
The report describes
an assault with scissors.

659
00:51:44,200 --> 00:51:45,360
That was the girl.

660
00:51:45,440 --> 00:51:46,600
That was the girl
that did that.

661
00:51:47,160 --> 00:51:52,200
Well, maybe she needs help,
too, but that's not our job. Okay?

662
00:51:55,960 --> 00:51:57,000
Okay.

663
00:52:33,320 --> 00:52:34,920
I'll be out back.

664
00:52:36,280 --> 00:52:38,920
I'm going to find
a tree to chop down.

665
00:52:43,840 --> 00:52:46,960
I do know what
you're feeling, Suzy-bean.

666
00:52:47,040 --> 00:52:50,960
I've had moments
myself where I say, "What am I doing here?"

667
00:52:51,080 --> 00:52:52,520
"Who made this decision?"

668
00:52:53,360 --> 00:52:56,520
"How could I allow myself
to do something so stupid?"

669
00:52:56,600 --> 00:52:58,920
"And why is it
still happening?"

670
00:53:00,720 --> 00:53:02,560
We women are more emotional...

