How'd you get here?

761
01:00:15,240 --> 01:00:16,880
They snuck me down
the laundry chute

762
01:00:16,960 --> 01:00:18,840
and left a papier-mch
dummy in my bed.

763
01:00:19,200 --> 01:00:22,200
Diversion tactics.
Good thinking.

764
01:00:39,560 --> 01:00:40,600
Where we going?

765
01:00:40,680 --> 01:00:41,720
Fort Lebanon.

766
01:00:41,800 --> 01:00:44,880
My cousin Ben runs the Supply and
Resources outpost for the Hullabaloo.

767
01:00:44,960 --> 01:00:48,200
He's a Falcon Scout,
Legionnaire. Cousin Ben'll know what to do.

768
01:00:48,280 --> 01:00:49,840
Can we trust him?

769
01:00:49,920 --> 01:00:51,720
Normally, I'd say no.

770
01:00:53,520 --> 01:00:55,360
Did you leave
another note for Lionel?

771
01:00:55,440 --> 01:00:57,520
Not this time.
He can't keep his trap shut.

772
01:00:57,600 --> 01:00:59,240
Besides, I'll probably
never see him again.

773
01:00:59,320 --> 01:01:00,360
True.

774
01:01:17,480 --> 01:01:19,960
This is the island
of St. Jack Wood,

775
01:01:20,040 --> 01:01:21,760
extending far north
from Land's End

776
01:01:21,840 --> 01:01:25,160
along the deep water channel
that leads to Broken Rock.

777
01:01:28,960 --> 01:01:32,880
A low flood plain separates the
beach from the township above.

778
01:01:32,960 --> 01:01:36,440
A small but
prosperous community.

779
01:01:36,520 --> 01:01:39,120
The barometer reads
28 inches and dropping.

780
01:01:39,200 --> 01:01:43,720
Strong winds, as you can see,
already at 22 knots.

781
01:01:46,760 --> 01:01:49,960
The time is now 4:35 a.m.

782
01:02:09,920 --> 01:02:14,400
Did you file the motion
of continuance? Peabody v. Henderson?

783
01:02:14,480 --> 01:02:15,720
It was sustained.

784
01:02:15,800 --> 01:02:17,080
Good.

785
01:02:18,640 --> 01:02:21,080
Did the judge consider
your application for leniency?

786
01:02:21,160 --> 01:02:22,520
Rogers v. Yentob?

787
01:02:22,600 --> 01:02:24,440
- He granted it.
- Great.

788
01:02:28,080 --> 01:02:29,600
I'm sorry, Walt.

789
01:02:32,000 --> 01:02:34,920
It's not your fault.

790
01:02:36,840 --> 01:02:40,640
Which injuries
are you apologizing for, specifically?

791
01:02:40,720 --> 01:02:43,040
Specifically?

792
01:02:43,120 --> 01:02:45,480
Whichever ones still hurt.

793
01:02:46,360 --> 01:02:48,840
Half of those
were self-inflicted.

794
01:02:55,280 --> 01:02:59,080
I hope the roof flies off,
and I get sucked up into space.

795
01:02:59,800 --> 01:03:01,560
You'll be better
off without me.

796
01:03:03,480 --> 01:03:06,000
Stop feeling
sorry for yourself.

797
01:03:09,280 --> 01:03:10,840
Why?

798
01:03:15,120 --> 01:03:17,280
We're all they've got, Walt.

799
01:03:25,080 --> 01:03:27,040
That's not enough.

800
01:03:35,560 --> 01:03:37,440
"'But I'm not going, '
said Barnaby Jack.

801
01:03:37,520 --> 01:03:38,800
"'I'm running away
tonight for good.

802
01:03:38,880 --> 01:03:41,000
"'And this time I
won't get caught.'

803
01:03:41,080 --> 01:03:43,400
"Annabelle whispered,
'I'm coming with you.'

804
01:03:43,480 --> 01:03:45,240
"Her yellow hair,
now brown at the roots,

805
01:03:45,360 --> 01:03:47,120
"caught up in
the wind and danced.

806
01:03:47,200 --> 01:03:48,800
"Barnaby Jack
took Annabelle's hand

807
01:03:48,880 --> 01:03:51,520
"and pressed something into it
the size of a jellybean.

808
01:03:51,600 --> 01:03:54,600
"'Hide this in your socks,
and be ready at midnight."'

809
01:03:57,440 --> 01:03:59,080
Continue.

810
01:03:59,160 --> 01:04:00,200
Keep going.

811
01:04:00,280 --> 01:04:01,760
- Keep going.
- Go on.

812
01:04:01,840 --> 01:04:02,960
- We're listening.
- That's good.

813
01:04:04,760 --> 01:04:08,600
"He leapt out the window
and landed in the fresh fallen snow."

814
01:04:14,120 --> 01:04:16,720
Where's my record player?

815
01:05:26,880 --> 01:05:28,400
You're not going to
believe this one, sir.

816
01:05:28,480 --> 01:05:32,480
That Scout Master on
New Penzance has now lost his entire troop.

817
01:05:37,120 --> 01:05:39,120
Well, I'll be damned!

818
01:05:39,240 --> 01:05:40,360
Who is this bimbo?

819
01:05:40,440 --> 01:05:41,600
Couldn't say, sir.

820
01:05:58,040 --> 01:05:59,560
Be right back.

821
01:06:03,760 --> 01:06:07,560
There's a broken gumball machine
right behind the snack tent.

822
01:06:09,160 --> 01:06:10,760
I don't care how they do it
where you come from.

823
01:06:10,840 --> 01:06:13,760
You want pop? You want candy?
You want a snake bite kit?

824
01:06:13,840 --> 01:06:14,960
Get some money.

825
01:06:15,040 --> 01:06:16,600
Cousin Ben?

826
01:06:16,680 --> 01:06:18,720
Come back in five minutes.

827
01:06:22,200 --> 01:06:23,240
Is this him?

828
01:06:23,320 --> 01:06:25,320
Field Mate Sam Shakusky,
Troop 55, resigned.

829
01:06:25,400 --> 01:06:27,200
He's hot. Almost too hot.
What's in the can?

830
01:06:27,280 --> 01:06:28,680
$76, but it's mostly
in nickels.

831
01:06:28,760 --> 01:06:29,840
Give it to me.

832
01:06:29,920 --> 01:06:31,560
- Your badge in seamanship?
- Yes, sir.

833
01:06:31,640 --> 01:06:34,040
Good. There's a cold water
crabber moored off Broken Rock.

834
01:06:34,120 --> 01:06:35,280
The skipper owes me an IOU.

835
01:06:35,360 --> 01:06:37,520
We'll see if he
can take you on as a claw cracker.

836
01:06:37,600 --> 01:06:39,520
It won't be an easy life,
but it's better than shock therapy.

837
01:06:39,600 --> 01:06:40,800
Thank you, sir.

838
01:06:40,880 --> 01:06:42,600
By the way,
where's the chapel tent?

839
01:06:42,680 --> 01:06:43,880
Back there,
but the padre's home with the mumps.

840
01:06:43,960 --> 01:06:45,120
Why do you ask?

841
01:06:45,200 --> 01:06:47,200
I want to bring my wife.

842
01:06:49,680 --> 01:06:51,080
But we're not married yet.

843
01:06:51,160 --> 01:06:52,280
You his girl?

844
01:06:52,360 --> 01:06:53,400
Yeah.

845
01:06:54,240 --> 01:06:56,280
Technically,
I'm a civil law scrivener.

846
01:06:56,360 --> 01:06:58,960
I'm authorized
to declare births, deaths, and marriages.

847
01:06:59,040 --> 01:07:00,640
You're kind of young.
You got a license?

848
01:07:00,720 --> 01:07:02,000
- No.
- No.

849
01:07:04,640 --> 01:07:06,520
I can't offer you
a legally binding union.

850
01:07:06,600 --> 01:07:08,080
It won't hold up in
the state, the county,

851
01:07:08,200 --> 01:07:09,560
or, frankly,
any courtroom in the world

852
01:07:09,640 --> 01:07:11,040
due to your age,
lack of a license,

853
01:07:11,120 --> 01:07:12,760
and failure to get
parental consent.

854
01:07:12,840 --> 01:07:15,400
But the ritual does
carry a very important

855
01:07:15,480 --> 01:07:17,200
moral weight within yourselves.

856
01:07:17,280 --> 01:07:20,240
You can't enter
into this lightly. Look into my eyes.

857
01:07:20,320 --> 01:07:22,000
- Do you love each other?
- Yes, we do.

858
01:07:22,080 --> 01:07:23,160
But think about
what I'm saying.

859
01:07:23,240 --> 01:07:24,280
Are you sure
you're ready for this?

860
01:07:24,360 --> 01:07:26,000
- Yes, we are.
- They're not listening to me.

861
01:07:26,080 --> 01:07:27,880
- Let me rephrase it.
- We're in a hurry.

862
01:07:27,960 --> 01:07:29,080
Are you chewing...

863
01:07:29,160 --> 01:07:30,560
Spit out the gum, sister.
In fact, everybody.

864
01:07:33,840 --> 01:07:35,080
I don't like
the snappy attitude.

865
01:07:35,160 --> 01:07:37,440
This is the most important decision
you've made in your lives.

866
01:07:37,520 --> 01:07:38,960
Go over by that trampoline
and talk it through

867
01:07:39,040 --> 01:07:41,800
before you give me
another quick answer.

868
01:07:59,640 --> 01:08:00,720
We're sure.

869
01:08:00,800 --> 01:08:02,800
Okay. Let's do a blood test.

870
01:08:02,880 --> 01:08:04,360
Under the eye of God,

871
01:08:04,440 --> 01:08:06,640
and within the boundaries of
this local jurisdiction,

872
01:08:06,720 --> 01:08:11,520
which we hereby consecrate on this
day, the 5th of September, 1965.

873
01:08:11,600 --> 01:08:12,680
That's the end
of the short form.

874
01:08:12,760 --> 01:08:14,720
Do any of the witnesses
have objections or remarks?

875
01:08:14,800 --> 01:08:17,160
Usually they don't. Skotak?

876
01:08:17,240 --> 01:08:19,440
Can we loan them the nickels?
I'm worried about their future.

877
01:08:19,520 --> 01:08:21,440
That's my fee.

878
01:08:21,520 --> 01:08:22,680
- What do you think?
- I don't know.

879
01:08:22,760 --> 01:08:26,160
What'd I just say?
That's my fee. I'm keeping the nickels.

880
01:08:34,720 --> 01:08:36,320
Okay, they can have
the tennis ball can.

881
01:08:37,080 --> 01:08:39,720
Sign here,
initial here and here.

882
01:08:40,600 --> 01:08:43,440
Take the carbon,
leave the Bible. Let's go.

883
01:10:12,560 --> 01:10:13,920
Where are they going, again?

884
01:10:14,000 --> 01:10:16,560
He's going to work on a shrimper,
if I understand correctly.

885
01:10:16,640 --> 01:10:18,560
- I wish them well.
- Me, too.

886
01:10:18,640 --> 01:10:20,440
Me, too.

887
01:10:20,520 --> 01:10:22,120
I think they're coming back.

888
01:10:25,120 --> 01:10:26,960
- Be quick, sailor!
- What happened?

889
01:10:27,280 --> 01:10:29,240
She left her
binoculars on a hook in the chapel tent.

890
01:10:30,280 --> 01:10:31,320
Just leave them.

891
01:10:31,400 --> 01:10:33,240
We can't. It's her magic power!

892
01:10:46,200 --> 01:10:49,000
You killed your dog,
by the way.

893
01:10:49,080 --> 01:10:50,520
Snoopy?

894
01:10:51,960 --> 01:10:53,360
Well, it couldn't be helped.

895
01:10:56,200 --> 01:10:57,840
Why do you
consider me your enemy?

896
01:10:59,520 --> 01:11:00,680
Because your
girlfriend stabbed me

897
01:11:00,760 --> 01:11:02,280
in the back with
lefty scissors.

898
01:11:03,160 --> 01:11:04,360
She's my wife now.

899
01:11:06,160 --> 01:11:07,440
Congratulations.

900
01:11:07,800 --> 01:11:11,640
Thank you, but I'm saying before
that, six weeks ago, from day one.

901
01:11:12,800 --> 01:11:14,640
Why don't you like me?

902
01:11:15,440 --> 01:11:18,600
Why should I? Nobody else does.

903
01:11:30,040 --> 01:11:32,640
My God! He's here!
The fugitive! Stop him!

904
01:11:32,720 --> 01:11:34,320
Stop him!

905
01:12:30,840 --> 01:12:33,200
On this spot,
I'll fight no more, forever.

906
01:12:33,280 --> 01:12:35,400
Come and get me, you bastards!

907
01:12:49,640 --> 01:12:51,120
I'm okay.

908
01:12:54,480 --> 01:12:55,520
Follow me.

909
01:13:02,640 --> 01:13:04,360
Company, let's go!

910
01:13:13,440 --> 01:13:15,120
Captain Sharp,
we've located the missing troop.

911
01:13:15,200 --> 01:13:17,280
They just fled camp.
We're in pursuit.

912
01:13:17,360 --> 01:13:19,000
They're accompanied
by a 12-year-old girl

913
01:13:19,080 --> 01:13:20,600
in knee socks
and Sunday school shoes.

914
01:13:20,680 --> 01:13:22,760
Stand by, Commander Pierce.

915
01:13:23,400 --> 01:13:25,080
Jed, re-route to St. Jack Wood.

916
01:13:25,160 --> 01:13:27,120
Tell Social Services
the boy's at Fort Lebanon.

917
01:13:27,200 --> 01:13:28,240
Roger that. Will comply.

918
01:13:28,320 --> 01:13:29,920
Notify the Bishops,
Suzy's there.

919
01:13:30,000 --> 01:13:31,080
Randy, you monitoring?

920
01:13:31,160 --> 01:13:33,280
Affirmative. I'm on my way.

921
01:13:34,480 --> 01:13:35,520
Hello?

922
01:13:35,600 --> 01:13:36,640
Hello, Mr. Bishop?

923
01:13:36,960 --> 01:13:38,640
Oh, dear God. Get the boys!

924
01:13:40,120 --> 01:13:41,760
Let's go! Right now!

925
01:13:42,280 --> 01:13:43,800
Tower control, this is Jed.

926
01:13:43,880 --> 01:13:47,880
Confirm coordinates for new
destination, Alpha two-two-seven-one-fiver.

927
01:13:47,960 --> 01:13:49,280
Looking pretty soupy up here.

928
01:13:49,360 --> 01:13:52,240
Wouldn't mind setting down
before the pot boils over.

929
01:13:52,320 --> 01:13:53,600
Hang on, Social Services.

930
01:14:13,440 --> 01:14:15,480
Once again, storm
waters have just breached

931
01:14:15,560 --> 01:14:17,240
the dam at
Black Beacon Reservoir.

932
01:14:17,320 --> 01:14:20,480
A flash flood alert is in effect.
Take immediate precautions

933
01:14:21,280 --> 01:14:23,040
That's coming our way.

934
01:14:23,120 --> 01:14:24,800
Did you find them?

935
01:14:24,880 --> 01:14:27,480
Prepare to mobilize
to higher ground.

936
01:14:29,800 --> 01:14:32,840
St. Jack's Church
is the designated storm shelter.

937
01:14:32,920 --> 01:14:35,920
Notify all Scouts to
muster outside my tent, on the double.

938
01:15:13,880 --> 01:15:15,880
Attention, company!

939
01:15:15,960 --> 01:15:17,560
Prepare for...

940
01:15:18,440 --> 01:15:19,760
Who's that?

941
01:15:30,040 --> 01:15:32,080
You call yourself
a Khaki Scout?

942
01:15:32,560 --> 01:15:33,600
Sorry, sir?

943
01:15:33,680 --> 01:15:36,200
Where's your goddamn troop,
you son of a bitch?

944
01:15:36,280 --> 01:15:37,640
You don't have them?

945
01:15:37,720 --> 01:15:40,080
They could get
killed out there!

946
01:15:41,520 --> 01:15:43,280
I'm field stripping
you of your command.

947
01:15:52,120 --> 01:15:53,560
Attention, company!

948
01:15:53,640 --> 01:15:55,880
Prepare for
emergency evacuation!

949
01:15:56,000 --> 01:15:58,320
Sir, do you have your medicine?

950
01:15:59,720 --> 01:16:01,520
I'll be right back.

951
01:16:35,840 --> 01:16:37,760
Hold your positions!

952
01:17:08,480 --> 01:17:09,960
Company secretary,
status report.

953
01:17:10,040 --> 01:17:11,680
All accounted for,
Scout Master!

954
01:17:11,760 --> 01:17:15,160
Okay, boys,
we're going to make a run for it! Fall in!

955
01:17:15,240 --> 01:17:17,480
Let's move!

956
01:17:17,560 --> 01:17:19,760
Come on, follow me!

957
01:17:43,120 --> 01:17:44,440
Who's in charge here?

958
01:17:44,920 --> 01:17:46,000
Randy, what happened?

959
01:17:46,080 --> 01:17:47,160
Take the commander off me!

960
01:17:48,840 --> 01:17:50,840
Suzy?

961
01:17:50,920 --> 01:17:53,160
Suzy? Sam?

962
01:17:53,240 --> 01:17:54,320
They ran away again.

963
01:17:57,120 --> 01:17:59,040
We got to go back out there.
I need volunteers.

964
01:17:59,120 --> 01:18:01,280
You, and you and you.

965
01:18:01,360 --> 01:18:03,200
- You?
- Are you all right?

966
01:18:03,280 --> 01:18:04,520
Of course I am.

967
01:18:17,200 --> 01:18:18,320
Where's the boy?

968
01:18:19,240 --> 01:18:20,440
We don't know yet.

969
01:18:20,800 --> 01:18:21,840
That's not acceptable.

970
01:18:22,600 --> 01:18:24,560
What do you
want me to say, lady?

971
01:18:24,640 --> 01:18:25,960
Somebody get
Jed a cup of coffee.

972
01:18:28,160 --> 01:18:29,800
- You're Captain Sharp.
- That's correct.

973
01:18:29,880 --> 01:18:32,880
I'm Social Services. I remanded the
boy into your personal custody.

974
01:18:32,960 --> 01:18:34,320
You're responsible
for his safety.

975
01:18:34,400 --> 01:18:36,800
I'm told that
he's just been struck by lightning.

976
01:18:36,880 --> 01:18:38,200
That's the first
I've heard of it.

977
01:18:38,280 --> 01:18:39,320
It's true.

978
01:18:39,400 --> 01:18:40,720
Scout Master Ward, I presume.

979
01:18:40,800 --> 01:18:41,840
Yes, ma'am.

980
01:18:41,920 --> 01:18:43,280
Your reputation precedes you.

981
01:18:43,800 --> 01:18:45,760
You two are
the most appallingly

982
01:18:45,840 --> 01:18:47,360
incompetent custodial guardians

983
01:18:47,440 --> 01:18:49,440
Social Services has
ever had the misfortune

984
01:18:49,520 --> 01:18:51,880
to encounter in
a 27-year career!

985
01:18:52,680 --> 01:18:54,240
What do you have to
say for yourselves?

986
01:18:54,320 --> 01:18:56,800
You can't do this.
They'll eat him alive in there.

987
01:18:56,880 --> 01:18:57,920
Where?

988
01:18:58,000 --> 01:18:59,440
What's the name
of the place again?

989
01:18:59,520 --> 01:19:02,400
Juvenile Refuge.

990
01:19:02,520 --> 01:19:04,120
Sounds like jail.

991
01:19:04,200 --> 01:19:08,960
Just find the boy,
and deliver him to Social Services.

992
01:19:09,080 --> 01:19:10,840
Nothing else is in your power.

993
01:19:10,920 --> 01:19:12,800
I'm sorry.
Can we get back to the rescue now?

994
01:19:12,920 --> 01:19:14,560
- Suzy is still out there.
- Who are you?

995
01:19:14,640 --> 01:19:16,760
Walt and Laura Bishop,
their daughter's the missing girl.

996
01:19:16,840 --> 01:19:17,880
The parents of the stabber?

997
01:19:17,960 --> 01:19:20,040
I object to that description.
She was attacked.

998
01:19:20,120 --> 01:19:21,160
Excuse me?

999
01:19:21,240 --> 01:19:23,520
I want the details about that.
Where's the Scout she knifed?

1000
01:19:23,600 --> 01:19:24,960
Right here.

1001
01:19:25,040 --> 01:19:27,000
- Field Mate Redford, sir.
- What's his condition?

1002
01:19:27,080 --> 01:19:28,640
He may suffer some limited
chronic kidney insufficiency.

1003
01:19:28,720 --> 01:19:29,760
Here's the report.

1004
01:19:29,840 --> 01:19:31,280
- We don't have time for that!
- She's right.

1005
01:19:31,360 --> 01:19:32,920
- Let's go.
- Stop!

1006
01:19:34,720 --> 01:19:36,400
Nobody's going anywhere.

1007
01:19:38,560 --> 01:19:40,720
He's not getting shock therapy.

1008
01:19:41,200 --> 01:19:44,920
That's it!
I am citing you for gross misconduct.

1009
01:19:45,040 --> 01:19:46,280
You are hereby
summoned to appear...

1010
01:19:46,360 --> 01:19:47,520
I'm writing you up back!

1011
01:19:47,600 --> 01:19:50,040
Be notified that
you stand accused of mistreatment...

1012
01:19:50,120 --> 01:19:51,160
What are you talking about?

1013
01:19:51,240 --> 01:19:52,280
I won't let you do it!

1014
01:19:52,360 --> 01:19:53,400
Look!

1015
01:20:01,960 --> 01:20:03,640
- They're gone.
- Who?

1016
01:20:03,720 --> 01:20:05,480
- Suzy?
- Sam!

1017
01:20:05,560 --> 01:20:06,600
- They're here?
- Yeah.

1018
01:20:06,680 --> 01:20:09,080
Where'd they go? Answer me!

1019
01:20:29,120 --> 01:20:31,400
Halt! Stop!

1020
01:20:37,000 --> 01:20:38,280
Stay there.

1021
01:20:38,360 --> 01:20:40,880
Wait, take these!

1022
01:20:55,560 --> 01:20:57,840
Where are you going?
What are you doing?

1023
01:20:57,920 --> 01:20:59,640
Come down!

1024
01:21:13,440 --> 01:21:15,680
Social Services,
do you read me? Over.

1025
01:21:35,720 --> 01:21:36,920
We might have to swim for it.

1026
01:21:38,880 --> 01:21:41,240
How deep is it?
I didn't bring my life jacket.

1027
01:21:41,720 --> 01:21:44,160
I don't know, but if it's too
shallow, we'll break our necks anyway.

1028
01:21:46,320 --> 01:21:47,680
Hang on to me.

1029
01:21:49,040 --> 01:21:50,280
Okay.

1030
01:21:51,760 --> 01:21:53,960
No, I'm not married, but
I'm a police officer.

1031
01:21:54,040 --> 01:21:55,800
Application denied. I'm sorry.

1032
01:21:55,920 --> 01:21:58,440
I cannot authorize that. Over.

1033
01:21:58,520 --> 01:22:00,920
Counselors, what's
the legal perspective? Over.

1034
01:22:01,600 --> 01:22:04,120
In this state,
I would litigate with extreme confidence.

1035
01:22:04,200 --> 01:22:05,960
- I concur.
- Open with Article 15

1036
01:22:06,040 --> 01:22:07,440
of the Codes of
Civic Jurisdiction.

1037
01:22:07,520 --> 01:22:09,320
No party,
under any circumstances,

1038
01:22:09,400 --> 01:22:10,880
shall be denied due
and proper consideration

1039
01:22:10,960 --> 01:22:12,440
without prejudice
in perpetuity.

1040
01:22:13,360 --> 01:22:14,520
On three again.

1041
01:22:14,600 --> 01:22:15,760
Wait.

1042
01:22:16,600 --> 01:22:18,960
Just in case this is a suicide

1043
01:22:19,040 --> 01:22:21,560
or they capture us
and we never see each other again anymore,

1044
01:22:21,640 --> 01:22:24,960
I just want to say
thank you for marrying me.

1045
01:22:26,280 --> 01:22:28,680
I'm glad I got
to know you, Suzy.

1046
01:22:41,200 --> 01:22:42,800
I think you've still
got lightning in you.

1047
01:22:43,200 --> 01:22:44,240
Let's jump.

1048
01:22:44,320 --> 01:22:45,920
No! God damn it!

1049
01:22:48,400 --> 01:22:49,640
Tell him. Over.

1050
01:22:49,720 --> 01:22:51,440
Captain Sharp is
offering to assume

1051
01:22:51,560 --> 01:22:53,200
the responsibility
of foster parenthood.

1052
01:22:54,200 --> 01:22:56,280
He wants you to live with him.

1053
01:22:56,680 --> 01:22:59,000
Is this acceptable to you, Mr. Shakusky?

1054
01:23:02,600 --> 01:23:03,840
What do you think, pal?

1055
01:23:14,640 --> 01:23:16,160
We're coming down.
Over and out.

1056
01:23:16,720 --> 01:23:18,120
They're coming down.
Over and...

1057
01:23:36,120 --> 01:23:38,080
Don't let go.

1058
01:23:45,480 --> 01:23:47,120
The Black Beacon
storm was considered

1059
01:23:47,200 --> 01:23:48,920
by the US Department
of Inclement Weather

1060
01:23:49,000 --> 01:23:51,880
to be the region's
most destructive meteorological event

1061
01:23:51,960 --> 01:23:54,840
of the second half
of the 20th century.

1062
01:23:55,520 --> 01:23:59,120
It lingered through six high
tides and inundated the islands

1063
01:23:59,200 --> 01:24:02,920
